==================================================
MILESTONE 2 — api-server MVP
==================================================

Context: Milestone 1 is complete. Repo is bootstrapped with full
directory structure, domain models, DB schema, seed data, Docker
Compose, and Go workspace at go 1.25.1.

==================================================
GOAL
==================================================

Implement a working api-server with:

1. packages/storage  — pgx v5 query layer (problems, submissions,
                        sessions, streak, reviews)
2. packages/queue    — asynq job type definitions (no real worker yet)
3. apps/api-server   — Gin HTTP server with all Milestone 2 endpoints

Submissions use a mock evaluator (goroutine, 500ms delay) — real
Docker execution is Milestone 6.

==================================================
CONSTRAINTS
==================================================

- No authentication in v1. All requests use a single hardcoded USER_ID
  read from env (default: 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001).
- No real judge worker. Submissions are evaluated by an in-process
  goroutine that returns "Accepted" for non-empty code.
- Redis / asynq is NOT required for Milestone 2. queue package defines
  types only; api-server uses goroutines for mock evaluation.
- Tags / pattern_tags in PostgreSQL are TEXT[] columns. pgx v5 scans
  them directly into []string.
- Enum columns (difficulty, provider, submission_status, language) are
  cast to TEXT in SELECT and compared as TEXT in WHERE to avoid pgx
  enum type registration.

==================================================
PACKAGES/STORAGE DESIGN
==================================================

Files:
  db.go          — DB struct, Connect(ctx, dsn) (*DB, error), Close()
  problems.go    — ProblemStore, ProblemFilter, List, GetByID, GetBySlug, Suggest
  submissions.go — SubmissionStore, Create, GetByID, UpdateVerdict, ListByUser
  sessions.go    — SessionStore, StartTimer, StopTimer, ActiveTimer,
                   RecordSubmission, GetOrCreateToday
  streak.go      — SessionStore.GetStreak → StreakInfo{Current, Longest, LastPracticed}
  reviews.go     — ReviewStore, GetDue

Key decisions:
- All stores hold a *DB (pgxpool wrapper).
- Constructors: NewProblemStore(db), NewSubmissionStore(db), etc.
- Shared rowScanner interface for single-row and multi-row scan helpers.
- scanProblem, scanSubmission, scanTimerSession as package-level helpers.
- ErrNoRows from pgx.ErrNoRows → return nil, nil (not found, not error).
- ProblemFilter.Difficulty and .Provider are pointers — nil means "no filter".
- Suggest query: NOT IN accepted submissions + prefer pattern overlap via
  ORDER BY CASE WHEN $2::text[] && pattern_tags THEN 0 ELSE 1 END, RANDOM()
- RecordSubmission(ctx, userID, accepted bool) — upserts daily_sessions,
  increments attempted_count always, solved_count only when accepted.
- StopTimer also adds elapsed_secs to daily_sessions.time_spent_secs.
- GetStreak fetches all practice dates sorted DESC, computes current and
  longest streak in Go by checking consecutive days.
- StreakInfo is defined in storage package (not domain) as a query result.

==================================================
PACKAGES/QUEUE DESIGN
==================================================

Files:
  jobs.go — TypeEvaluateSubmission constant + EvaluatePayload struct

Not wired into api-server for Milestone 2. Defined now so Milestone 6
(judge-worker) can import without changes.

==================================================
APPS/API-SERVER DESIGN
==================================================

Files:
  main.go           — parse config, connect DB, start server
  config.go         — Config struct, LoadConfig() from env
  server.go         — Server struct, New, Run, registerRoutes
  handler/
    handler.go      — Handler struct with all stores + UserID
    problems.go     — ListProblems, GetProblem, SuggestProblem
    submissions.go  — CreateSubmission, GetSubmission, ListSubmissions
    progress.go     — GetProgressToday, GetStreak
    timers.go       — StartTimer, StopTimer, CurrentTimer
    reviews.go      — GetReviewsToday

Config env vars (all have defaults for local dev):
  DATABASE_URL  default: postgres://judgeloop:judgeloop@localhost:5432/judgeloop?sslmode=disable
  PORT          default: 8080
  USER_ID       default: 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001

Mock evaluator (in submissions.go):
  - Launched as goroutine on CreateSubmission
  - Sleeps 500ms
  - Accepts if code is non-empty, WrongAnswer otherwise
  - Calls UpdateVerdict + RecordSubmission on DB

==================================================
API ENDPOINTS (Milestone 2)
==================================================

GET  /api/problems
  Query: difficulty, tag, pattern, provider, limit (default 20), offset (default 0)
  Response: { "problems": [...], "total": N }

GET  /api/problems/suggest
  Response: single problem object (or 404 if none available)

GET  /api/problems/:id
  Tries UUID parse first, falls back to slug lookup
  Response: problem object or 404

POST /api/submissions
  Body: { "problem_id", "language", "code", "session_id"? }
  Response: { "submission_id", "status": "pending" }
  Side effect: spawns mock evaluator goroutine

GET  /api/submissions/:id
  Response: submission object with verdict fields

GET  /api/submissions/history
  Query: problem_id?, limit (default 20)
  Response: { "submissions": [...], "total": N }

GET  /api/progress/today
  Response: { "date", "solved", "attempted", "time_spent_minutes", "streak" }

GET  /api/streak
  Response: { "current", "longest", "last_practiced" }

POST /api/timers/start
  Body: { "problem_id"? }
  Response: { "id", "started_at" }

POST /api/timers/stop
  Body: {}
  Response: { "elapsed_seconds" }

GET  /api/timers/current
  Response: { "active": bool, "started_at"?, "elapsed_seconds"?, "problem_id"? }

GET  /api/reviews/today
  Response: { "reviews": [{ "problem_id", "slug", "title", "last_solved", "days_overdue" }] }

